#: ../../../docs/sphinx-extension.rst:5
msgid ""
"``sphinxcontrib_rust`` is a Sphinx extension that parses the Sphinx "
"directives and roles for the ``rust`` domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/sphinx-extension.rst:7
msgid ""
"The extension is tightly coupled with the :rust:exe:`sphinx-rustdocgen` "
"executable, which generates the appropriate content for the extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/sphinx-extension.rst:10
msgid ""
"It *can* be used without the Rust executable itself, by directly using the "
"directives in the reStructuredText or Markdown files. But that will result "
"in a lot more typing for you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/sphinx-extension.rst:13
msgid ""
"The documentation here is primarily meant for potential contributors and "
"developers, who want to add features or fix bugs. Users should read the "
"documentation in :ref:`usage` and/or :ref:`details`, or submit an issue."
msgstr ""

